From: Lukas Klizas <lukas@klizas.lt>
Date: Thu, 17 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amd/display: add dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns module
 parameter

Add a module parameter to override the DRAM clock change latency the
Display Mode Library uses when deciding whether memory pstate switching
is safe. On the Navi 14 dGPUs in the 2019 16" MacBookPro (Radeon Pro
5300M / 5500M), the hardcoded 404 us in dcn2_0_nv14_soc exceeds the
vblank hiding budget of the internal 3072x1920 retina panel, so the DML
marks mclk switching unsupported and the dGPU stays pinned at its
highest memory pstate whenever the panel is lit.

Default of 0 keeps existing per-ASIC behavior. When set to a non-zero
value, it is wired through init_data.bb_overrides.dram_clock_change_latency_ns
in amdgpu_dm_init.

Signed-off-by: Lukas Klizas <lukas@klizas.lt>
---
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu.h b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu.h
index b20a06abb..82dcc92a4 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu.h
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu.h
@@ -210,6 +210,7 @@ extern uint amdgpu_dc_feature_mask;
 extern uint amdgpu_freesync_vid_mode;
 extern uint amdgpu_dc_debug_mask;
 extern uint amdgpu_dc_visual_confirm;
+extern int amdgpu_dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns;
 extern int amdgpu_dm_abm_level;
 extern int amdgpu_backlight;
 extern int amdgpu_damage_clips;
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_drv.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_drv.c
index 83567ade8..9b617e951 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_drv.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_drv.c
@@ -891,6 +891,19 @@ module_param_named(dcdebugmask, amdgpu_dc_debug_mask, uint, 0444);
 MODULE_PARM_DESC(visualconfirm, "Visual confirm (0 = off (default), 1 = MPO, 5 = PSR)");
 module_param_named(visualconfirm, amdgpu_dc_visual_confirm, uint, 0444);

+/**
+ * DOC: dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns (int)
+ * Override the DRAM clock change latency in nanoseconds used by the Display
+ * Mode Library for pstate switching decisions. The default of 0 uses the
+ * hardware-specific value (404000 ns for DCN 2.0 dGPU). Lower values allow
+ * memory clock switching at higher display resolutions but risk display
+ * corruption if set below the actual hardware retraining time.
+ */
+int amdgpu_dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns;
+MODULE_PARM_DESC(dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns,
+	"Override DRAM clock change latency in ns for display pstate switching (0 = use default)");
+module_param_named(dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns, amdgpu_dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns, int, 0444);
+
 /**
  * DOC: abmlevel (uint)
  * Override the default ABM (Adaptive Backlight Management) level used for DC
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/amdgpu_dm/amdgpu_dm.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/amdgpu_dm/amdgpu_dm.c
index 62622aa62..1d8c7c169 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/amdgpu_dm/amdgpu_dm.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/display/amdgpu_dm/amdgpu_dm.c
@@ -2017,6 +2017,10 @@ static int amdgpu_dm_init(struct amdgpu_device *adev)
 	else
 		init_data.bb_from_dmub = NULL;

+	if (amdgpu_dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns > 0)
+		init_data.bb_overrides.dram_clock_change_latency_ns =
+			amdgpu_dc_dram_clock_change_latency_ns;
+
 	/* Display Core create. */
 	adev->dm.dc = dc_create(&init_data);
